Rating: 4
Ok, we love this! I took suggestions to up the flavor, and also had to make some substitutions to use what ingredients I had, & I think it helped the flavor. I didn't have white wine open, so I used Marsala. Since I was cooking whole wheat pasta the darker color did't cause any issues for us. Another substitute was a bunch of rainbow chard for the spininch I cooked the onions until they were very carmalized, bumping the flavor, and I had seasoned the peppers with oregano and dried basil when roasting. Extra red pepper flakes, black pepper & thyme also boosted the flavor. I'm going to make this in the fall with roasted butternut squash instead of peppers and goat cheese. Highly recommend!

