Rating: 3
very good. Having made this 2x now I have a few suggestions: 1.) Roasting your own peppers is cool if you've never tried it before, but you can substitute store bought in water or oil and get the exact same effect and cut 50% of the time and effort of this dish. 2.) Another reviewer suggested 1/2 teaspoon of red pepper flakes, and if you like a little kick to your dishes I would recommend this as well. 3.) In my experience about 1/2 the amount of Parmesan made the dish much cleaner and lighter, allowing the wine thyme and peppers to come out clearer. Thanks for the great recipe!

Rating: 4
Great taste, wonderful color & fresh - Will continue revamping - Here's my changes: Used full can of beef broth (14oz) and 1/2C sherry cooking wine to give more depth/flavor since rotini is so big (If using low/no sodium broth, add kosher salt for best flavor at time onions are "sweating"); Used jar of roasted red peppers soaked in H20 & vinegar to save time. Husband LOVED it all! Next time, will try feta, black olives, meat and/or 'shrooms - COOK'S TIP: Roast pine nuts B4 cooking so you avoid being distracted w/burners and oven -I burned a huge batch, such a waste :-(

