Rating: 4
Wow...I'm really surprised by the two previous reviews of this recipe. I saw the recipe in the Nov. issue and tried it as I had the ingredients on hand. I think this is one of the best pasta dishes ever. Not only does it have great taste, but the different textures of the pasta, spinach and pine nuts make it a joy to eat. I only used a cup of chopped onions (personal preference), and I used two 7 oz. jars of roasted red peppers for ease. Also, the only dry white wine I had on hand was a dry Riesling, which worked very well in this dish. I can't wait to make it for friends sometime. I'd love to see some others try this dish and hear what they think, too.

